CHANGES IN VERSION 0.99.22
--------------------------

NEW FEATURES

    o Added the granges_to_ucsc() function, which is the reverse of
        ucsc_to_granges().


CHANGES IN VERSION 0.99.21
--------------------------

NEW FEATURES

    o Added the function corner() which takes head of rows and columns of objects

CHANGES IN VERSION 0.99.20
--------------------------

SIGNIFICANT USER-VISIBLE CHANGES

    o agePlotter(): changed how the X-axis ticks and range are made for the
        prenatal samples.

CHANGES IN VERSION 0.99.19
--------------------------

NEW FEATURES

    o Introduced the ucsc_to_granges() function that converts a character vector
        of coordinates from the UCSC genome browser to a GRanges object.


CHANGES IN VERSION 0.99.18
--------------------------

SIGNIFICANT USER-VISIBLE CHANGES

    o agePlotter() is now more flexible and can handle up a vector of
        \code{pointColor} and \code{lineColor}. Also, the breaks
        are now flexible and support more scenarios (you need at least 3 groups).

CHANGES IN VERSION 0.99.16
--------------------------

SIGNIFICANT USER-VISIBLE CHANGES

    o GitHub repo is now public.

CHANGES IN VERSION 0.99.15
--------------------------

NEW FEATURES

    o Added the function expression_cutoff() which finds suggested expression
        cutoffs for an RPKM matrix.


CHANGES IN VERSION 0.99.14
--------------------------

BUG FIXES

    o Corrected the documentation of cleaningY(). This is after Stephen
        Semick and Emily Burke reported issues with the function.



CHANGES IN VERSION 0.99.13
--------------------------

SIGNIFICANT USER-VISIBLE CHANGES

    o Moved coverage_bwtool() to the recount.bwtool package.


CHANGES IN VERSION 0.99.12
--------------------------

NEW FEATURES

    o Added the function coverage_bwtool() for computing coverage matrices
        using bwtool for a user-specified list of bigWig files and a
        user-specified phenotype table. It's heavily based on recount.bwtool

CHANGES IN VERSION 0.99.11
--------------------------

SIGNIFICANT USER-VISIBLE CHANGES

    o junctionCount() uses check.names = FALSE when calling DataFrame().
        Related to a bug Badoi Phan reported.


CHANGES IN VERSION 0.99.8
-------------------------

BUG FIXES

    o Added code by Emily Burke that makes junctionCount() work for single-end
        libraries. Still need to trace why ? are being added as the strand.

CHANGES IN VERSION 0.99.10
--------------------------

NEW FEATURES

    o Added the getT() function

CHANGES IN VERSION 0.99.7
-------------------------

NEW FEATURES

    o Added agePlotter() -- missing examples and tests

CHANGES IN VERSION 0.99.6
-------------------------

NEW FEATURES

    o Added junctionCount() -- missing examples and tests

CHANGES IN VERSION 0.99.5
-------------------------

NEW FEATURES

    o Added getR2() -- missing examples and tests

CHANGES IN VERSION 0.99.4
-------------------------

NEW FEATURES

    o Added cleaningY() -- missing examples and tests

CHANGES IN VERSION 0.99.3
-------------------------

NEW FEATURES

    o Added getOR()

CHANGES IN VERSION 0.99.2
-------------------------

SIGNIFICANT USER-VISIBLE CHANGES

    o Dropped splitit() since it's available in rafalib.
    o Now depending on rafalib making those functions available to the user.


CHANGES IN VERSION 0.99.0
-------------------------

NEW FEATURES

    o Added ss() as a wrapper for string split and sapply.
    o Added splitit() and split0() that split a vector into a list and return
        the integer indexes of the elements.
    o Added getPcaVars() which computes the percent of variance explained
        for the principal components of prcomp object.
    o Added getF().
